'''Alaine Rodin''' is an [[United States|American]] operatic [[soprano]] who has sung leading roles both in the United States and internationally. 

==Biography==
A native of Berkeley California, she studied at the [[San Francisco Conservatory]] and the [[Juilliard School]] and trained with the [[Lyric Opera of Chicago]]'s Young Artists programme, appearing in the LOC company premiere of [[John Corigliano|Corigliano]]'s ''[[The Ghosts of Versailles]]'' in 1990.<ref name = "Bullock">Bullock, Ken, [http://www.berkeleydailyplanet.com/issue/2006-10-20/article/25378?headline=A-Homecoming-For-Alaine-Rodin&status=301 "A Homecoming For Alaine Rodin"], ''[[Berkeley Daily Planet]]'', 20 October 2006 (accessed 1 May 2010) </ref><ref>[[Lyric Opera of Chicago]], [http://www.lyricopera.org/about/cast_1990.aspx Cast lists 1990-1999]</ref> She went on to sing Woglinde in ''[[Das Rheingold]]'' ([[New Orleans Opera]]), Antonia in ''[[Les contes d'Hoffmann]]'' (Opera Lirico de Costa Rica), Li<U+00F9> in ''[[Turandot]]'' ([[Guatemala City]]) and Marguerite in ''[[Faust (opera)|Faust]]'' (Augusta Opera). Rodin first came to international attention when appeared in the 1996-1997 Broadway performances of [[Terrence McNally]]'s ''[[Master Class]]'', where she sang "Vieni t'affretta" from Verdi's ''[[Macbeth (opera)|Macbeth]]''.<ref>Marks, Peter [http://www.nytimes.com/1997/03/01/theater/a-new-callas-more-wounded-than-wounding.html?pagewanted=1 "A New Callas More Wounded Than Wounding"], ''New York Times'', 1 March 1997 (accessed 1 May 2010)</ref> She made her European d<U+00E9>but as Micaela in ''[[Carmen]]'' at the [[Op<U+00E9>ra Comique]] in Paris in February 1999.<ref>[[Op<U+00E9>ra national du Rhin]], [http://guschlbauer.com/Progr/vol52.pdf Saison 1998-1999], 1998, Vol. 52 p. 13 (in French, accessed 1 May 2010)</ref> 

In 2007, she appeared at the [[Utah Festival Opera]] as Clara in ''[[Porgy and Bess]]'' and with West Bay Opera as Liza in ''[[The Queen of Spades (opera)|The Queen of Spades]]''.<ref>Howard, Rebecca C. [http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-7515205.html "Utah Festival Opera's 4 productions a little uneven"], ''[[Deseret Morning News]]'',  16 July 2007 (accessed via subscription 1 May 2010)</ref><ref>Kreitman, Keith, [http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-5806907.html "'Queen of Spades' deals strong hand"], ''[[Oakland Tribune]], 22 February 2007 (accessed via subscription 1 May 2010)</ref> As a member of the [[Linz]] Landestheater opera company during the 2008/2009 and 2009/2010 seasons, she has sung the title role in [[Dmitri Shostakovich| Shostakovich]]'s ''[[Lady Macbeth of the Mtsensk District (opera)|Lady Macbeth of Mtensk]]'', Countess Almaviva in ''[[Le nozze di Figaro]]'', Giulietta in ''Les contes d'Hoffmann'' and First Soprano in [[Philip Glass]]' opera ''[[Kepler (opera)|Kepler]]'', as well as singing with the company for the opera's North American premiere at the [[Brooklyn Academy of Music]].<ref>Linz Landestheater, [http://www.landestheater-linz.at/495_DE-Ensemble-Opernensemble.639AAF9400132ce70dbe9cbce03fbc58475060814 Opernensemble Spielzeit 2009/2010] (Opera ensemble, 2009/2010 Season) (in German, accessed 1 May 2010)</ref><ref>''Ober<U+00F6>sterreichische Nachrichten'', [http://www.nachrichten.at/nachrichten/kultur/art16,296979 "Keplers Weltbild erobert New York"], 26 March 2010 (in German, accessed 1 May 2010)</ref><ref>Persch<U+00E9>, Gerhard , [http://www.kultiversum.de/Oper-Opernwelt/Panorama-Karikatur-und-Tragik.html "Karikatur-und-Tragik"], ''Opernwelt'', July 2009, p. 48, reprinted on ''Kultiversum'' (in German, accessed 1 May 2010)</ref>

Her appearances on the concert stage have included those at [[Sarasota Opera]]<ref>Hulsking, Charlie, [http://news.google.co.uk/newspapers?id=1G8fAAAAIBAJ&sjid=ZH8EAAAAIBAJ&pg=4372,3581737&dq=alaine-rodin&hl=en Broadway Visits the Opera], ''[[Sarasota Herald-Tribune]]'', 3 November 2000, p. 33 (accessed 1 May 2010)</ref> and the [[Kyoto]] International Music Festival.

